### File Upload API Tests

# Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8081/api
@authToken = Bearer your_jwt_token_here

### Upload Profile Image
POST {{baseUrl}}/files/profile-image
Authorization: {{authToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="profile.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< path/to/your/test/image.jpg
--boundary--

### Delete Profile Image
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/files/profile-image
Authorization: {{authToken}}

### Example response for successful upload:
# {
#   "message": "Profile image uploaded successfully",
#   "imageUrl": "/api/uploads/profile-images/filename.jpg"
# }

### Example response for successful delete:
# {
#   "message": "Profile image deleted successfully"
# }

### Notes:
# 1. Replace 'your_jwt_token_here' with a valid JWT token from login
# 2. Replace 'path/to/your/test/image.jpg' with an actual image file path
# 3. Supported formats: JPG, PNG, GIF, WebP (max 5MB)
# 4. The uploaded image will be stored in uploads/profile-images/ directory
# 5. The image URL returned includes the API context path (/api)
# 6. Deleting an image will reset the user's profile image to default role-based avatar